# DeFi Explained in 60 Seconds (AI Video Script)

DeFi, or Decentralized Finance, is a blockchain-based financial system without banks.

Instead of trusting institutions, DeFi uses smart contracts to automate transactions.

With DeFi, users can trade, lend, and borrow crypto assets directly from their wallets.

Everything is transparent, permissionless, and runs on blockchain technology.

DeFi is changing how people access financial services worldwide.
